# Canonical author identity for this Substrate.
#
# The repository's history carries eight spellings of one person: names that
# drifted as different tooling committed on the Botanist's behalf (the early
# Antigravity / Codex / Claude era), plus the original personal commit. They are
# one identity, and this file says so for `git log`, `git shortlog` and
# `git blame`.
#
# WHAT THIS FIXES AND WHAT IT DOES NOT.
#
# A .mailmap normalises how git DISPLAYS an author. GitHub does not read it:
# GitHub attributes a commit by matching the author email to a verified email on
# an account. So the 44 commits authored as opentendril@noreply.github.com or
# bot@opentendril.com — neither of which is linked to the account — remain
# unattributed on GitHub no matter what this file says. Only rewriting history
# changes that, and the earliest of them is the ROOT COMMIT, so the rewrite would
# be the whole repository.
#
# Attribution (which account owns a commit) is decided by the EMAIL.
# Verification (the green badge) is decided by the SIGNING KEY. Two separate
# mechanisms; 273992813+opentendril@users.noreply.github.com is the account's
# GitHub noreply address, not a key.

